bergmark_d wrote:

&gt;
&gt; OK, we are getting there (and I&#39;m grateful the Heritrix team is taking
&gt; this problem on).  The AList is just such a handy place to stuff
&gt; application-related information.  My desire is to pass info from the
&gt; parent CrawlURI&#39;s AList to the child CandidateURI (who currently does
&gt; not have an AList -- I wish it did!).  I guess I&#39;ll have to subclass
&gt; CandidateURI to get this. 
&gt;
&gt; So a protected createCandidateURI is a promising direction.  If this
&gt; method could take the parent CrawlURI as well as the other stuff and
&gt; return a new CandidateURI, then all might be possible.  Could you add
&gt; curi to the arguments passed to createCandidateURI?  Or maybe it would
&gt; be neater to pass just the curi&#39;s AList to the method? 

Here is the signature for the new method:

protected CandidateURI createCandidateURI(CrawlURI curi, UURI base,
            String link)

It already takes the link&#39;s parent page curi -- or do you mean something 
else.

As to the AList issue, thats a bit tougher.  Seems little point setting 
you up if there is no place to stuff data to carry across the crawl. 
Looking at the creation of the CrawlURI from the CandidateURI over in 
the Frontier, the way it currently works is that a new CrawlURI instance 
is created and a set of CandidateURI data is copied into it.  So you&#39;ll 
need to have overrides in this location too to get your appended 
CandidateURI data added the new CrawlURI instance.

We&#39;re having a chat here in-house looking at a couple of things.  We&#39;ll 
be back to you hopefully with a proposal that gets you what you need.

St.Ack


